summary: Pokemon Company To Talk About Next Pokemon Game For Nintendo Switch In 2019
title: Pokemon Company To Talk About Next Pokemon Game For Nintendo Switch In 2019
body:
Pokemon Company To Talk About Next Pokemon Game For Nintendo Switch In 2019

Eurogamer recently managed to secure some time with Junichi Masuda, who is the executive director and head of game development over at Game Freak, as well as designer Kensaku Nabana. The interview is wide-ranging and covers a number of topics about the upcoming Pokemon: Let’s Go!games which are due to be released next month. A lot of you are interested to see what the next core Pokemon game will…

blog.name: weirdandwackypokefusions
blog.title: Well that's strange!
blog.description:
Welcome!  I create, using the all-mighty classic Microsoft XP Paint, my own pokemon fusions. All the sprites come from pokestadium and usually people on deviantart/ the xy/sun&moon sprite project. I don't own any of the sprite used, I just fuse them! 
REQUESTS ARE OPEN! Ask Box: 3/15.
PLEASE FEEL FREE TO DRAW MY FUSIONS!!  I absolutely love it when people draw them! There's no need to ask either! Just make sure you tag me so them I can see it!
I hope you enjoy my fusions!

summary: Tegummyursa Teddiursa and Gummy Bear fusion Nutritional Information Sugar Type Ability: Rubbery skin - This pokefood cannot be...
caption:
Tegummyursa

Teddiursa and Gummy Bear fusion

Nutritional Information

Sugar Type

Ability: Rubbery skin - This pokefood cannot be damaged by physical attacks except cutting attacks as they bounce off its body.

Signature Move: Bouncing Body - The user stands still and lets attacks bounce off of its body. Protects the user for one turn and, if the opponent uses a move the move will bounce back at the opponent, damaging it for 10% of the move’s power.

The No-Eyed Pokefood

This pokefood can’t see so it makes its body super bouncy to try and deflect attacks. This pokefood can come in many colours and can have many letters on its stomach. 

Day 9 and we have a teddiursa and a gummy bear fusion suggested by @xxxxx-what-xxxxx. I hope you like it!
